## Mathematical Topologies\
\
### 1. AbsMean Ternary Compression ($b1.58$)\
Tensors are projected into a ternary matrix space via channel-wise scaling functions:\
$$\\gamma = \\frac\{1\}\{N\}\\sum_\{j=1\}^\{N\}|W_\{ij\}|$$\
$$W_\{q\} = \\text\{round\}\\left(\\text\{clip\}\\left(\\frac\{W\}\{\\gamma + \\epsilon\}, -1, 1\\right)\\right)$$\
\
### 2. Extreme Binary Hard Fork ($b1.0$)\
Research lineage forces zero-centered structures directly onto sign boundaries:\
$$\\alpha = \\frac\{1\}\{N\}\\sum_\{j=1\}^\{N\}|W_\{ij\}|, \\quad W_\{bin\} = \\text\{sign\}(W + \\epsilon)$$\
\
### 3. Gradient Inversion Routing\
To enable Quantization-Aware Training (QAT), non-differentiable ternary operators are embedded with custom Straight-Through Estimators (STE):\
$$\\frac\{\\partial W_\{q\}\}\{\\partial W\} \\approx 1$$\
